Phase 3-A: CORS Origin Restriction
Issue mapping: Addresses #3
What: Replace cors: true with explicit origin allowlist in all three Cloud Functions.

IMPORTANT — Firebase Functions v2 API note:
The onRequest() cors option accepts boolean | string | string[] | RegExp.
It does NOT accept a middleware-style config object ({ origin, methods, allowedHeaders, maxAge }).
Those options come from the cors npm package, which this project does not use.
Firebase handles methods, allowedHeaders, and maxAge internally when given an origin allowlist.

