Phase 3-B: Persistent Rate Limiter (Firestore-Backed)
Issue mapping: Addresses #4
What: Replace in-memory Map rate limiter with Firestore TTL documents that survive cold starts and scale across instances.

Architecture:
1. RateLimiter interface (rateLimiterTypes.ts) — async contract with checkRateLimit() returning Promise<boolean>
2. InMemoryRateLimiter (inMemoryRateLimiter.ts) — existing logic wrapped in async interface, used by tests and emulator
3. FirestoreRateLimiter (firestoreRateLimiter.ts) — Firestore transaction-based, used in production
4. RateLimiterFactory (rateLimiterFactory.ts) — selects implementation based on environment:
   - K_SERVICE set + not emulator → Firestore (lazy dynamic import to avoid test failures)
   - Otherwise → in-memory
5. rateLimiter.ts — async facade that all handlers import from (backward-compatible API)

