Phase 3-C: Auth Token Exposure Mitigation (Signed URL Approach)
Issue mapping: Addresses #11
What: Eliminate auth tokens from URL query params using short-lived HMAC-signed URLs.

IMPORTANT — Architecture decision:
The original plan proposed a separate signImageUrl Cloud Function that clients call before loading each image. This was rejected because:
- For a workspace with 10 link previews, it adds 10 extra HTTP round-trips before images start loading.
- The rate limit (10 req/min) would be exhausted immediately on workspace load.
Instead, signed proxy URLs are embedded directly in the fetchLinkMeta response. The server already fetches link metadata and knows the image URL — it returns pre-signed proxy URLs, eliminating the extra round-trip entirely.

